    • add

      public boolean add​(T element, int priority)
      Adds an element to the set with a specified priority. If the set already contains the element, the element is ignored and the method returns false.
      Parameters:
      element - element to add to the set
      priority - priority to assign to the element
      Returns:
      true iff the element was not already in the set.

    • getPriority

      public java.lang.Integer getPriority​(T element)

      Returns:
      the priority of the specified element, null if the element is not in the set.

    • changePriority

      public boolean changePriority​(T element, int priority)
      Changes the priority of an element in a set. If the element is not in the set, the element is added to the set.
      Parameters:
      element - element to change the priority of
      priority - priority to assign to the element
      Returns:
      true iff the element was not in the set already or if the element had a different priority prior to the call.
